						<summary>

						<p>Pillar lying in the survey No. 483 to the east of the village.</p>						

						<p>SADĀŚIVADĒVARĀYA.</p>						

						<p>1546 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Śaka [1468], Parābhava, Chaitra, śu. 11, [Monday], corresponding to March 13, 1546 A.D. The week day is Saturday.</p>						

						<p>It registers the remission of certain taxes vix, <hi rend="italic">Doṁmari paṁnu, Siddhāyaṁ</hi> on barbers <hi rend="italic">(Maṁgaḍlavāri paṁnu)</hi> of Kolavaḷi situated in Naṁdēla by Naṁdēla Tiṁmarāju with the permission of Rāmarāju and Sadāśivadēva mahārāya.</p>						

						</summary>
